ensation.go` | Populate `Transcript` in `CondenseResult` |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` | Add `generateTrailTitleFromTranscript()`, wire after condensation |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/auto_commit.go` | Wire `generateTrailTitleFromTranscript()` after save |\\n\\n## Design Decisions\\n\\n1. **`TextGenerator` optional interface** — follows existing pattern (like `TranscriptAnalyzer`, `HookSupport`). Agents opt in when their CLI supports non-interactive generation. Claude Code implements it today; Gemini/OpenCode can add it later.\\n2. **Haiku model** — trail titles are simple; haiku is fast (~1-2s) and cheap\\n3. **One-time gate** — `Description != \\\"\\\"` ensures LLM is only called on first condensation per trail\\n4. **Settings gate** — reuses `settings.IsSummarizeEnabled()`; no new setting\\n5. **Graceful skip** — if agent doesn't implement `TextGenerator`, title stays as prompt-derived; no error shown to user\\n6. **No `ClaudeGenerator` refactor** — existing summarize code works; trail titles use `TextGenerator` directly\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\\n```\\n\\nManual test:\\n1. Create a branch, enable entire with `summarize.enabled: true`\\n2. Run a Claude Code session, make a commit\\n3. Check `entire trail` output — should show LLM-generated title and description\\n4. Make a second commit — title should NOT be regenerated (description already set)\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/dip/.claude/projects/-Users-dip-Repositories-cli/6edd18ba-782c-4019-88d9-018079feea08.jsonl\"},\"uuid\":\"b765999a-2f8b-4063-ba1f-7b4a01b5e447\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T19:06:06.828Z\",\"planContent\":\"# Plan: LLM-Generated Trail Titles & Descriptions (Agent-Aware)\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nParts A (checkpoints.json) and B (prompt-based titles) are already implemente